fields.name: Revelations when you're high
fields.description: My freedom begins where many other people's freedom ends. That's roughly what we thought when, once again, after breaking a couple of common sense irrelevant laws about private property, we were sitting on a beautiful house called 'Corona' in the center of Berlin. Public spaces that belong to everyone, but no one is allowed to be there. Because that's the way the world works. But every time I found myself in a different reality, wading through the maze of underground utilities, in which the devil himself would break his neck, or talking on the edge of the roof with friends under the scent of a summer night and watching the last star go out over the city, giving way to a fiery dawn, in these moments I felt truly alive, renewed. This escape from the ordinary saved me.
